Quote:   `Tongue-murdering' appears to be a new term applied to slandering a man, or `putting his pot on' with intent to do him harm. At least it is a new term to this writer ... [and] was used during the hearing of an assault case at Lyttelton. ... using some kerbstone language with much emphasis ... `You've tongue-murdered me ...
